body:
Thank you for introducing special workspaces.

Are the any plans to introduces scratchpad/special workspace that can be toggled with the same keybinding to show/launch and hide an app? Similar to how qtile and xmonad handle scrachpads?
Example:
`bind = SUPER , grave , togglescratchpad sp-term`
```
if (sp-term.worspace == activeworkspace) {
  sp-term.workspace = special workspace
}
else  {
  if (sp-term is not spawned) {
    exec sp-term.command
  }
  sp-term.workspace = activeworkspace
}
```
sorry I used JS style syntax as that is what I am most familiar with

I find the current implementation very limiting and I believe a lot of people will find this a deal breaker for such a nicely feature compositor.

FYI
Right now [pyprland](https://github.com/hyprland-community/pyprland) tries to achieve this but is not ideal and it would be great to have this supported natively.

